Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportDensityMap(25.10)                                reportDensityMap(25.10)

Name
       reportDensityMap - Generates a map that uses colors to represent place-
       ment density and generates a placement density report

Syntax
       reportDensityMap

       [-help]

       [-gridInMicron <microns>] [-gridInRow <numberRows>]

       [-ignoreBlock {true|false}]

       [-ignoreFiller {true|false}]

       [-threshold <density>]

       Generates  a  map  that  uses colors to represent placement density and
       generates a placement density report. If you run this  command  without
       parameters,  it  generates  a map with a threshold of 0.75 and measures
       the grid in row height.

       Note: You can also use setDensityMapMode  to  set  the  threshold,  and
       specify whether the map displays bins in microns or rows.

       Use this command any time after placement.

       Use the Display Density Map form to select colors and step-size for the
       density levels in the map.

Parameters
       -gridInMicron <microns>
              Specifies  the  horizontal or vertical dimension of a bin in the
              map, measured in microns.

              Default: 50

              Upper limit: 1000

       -gridInRow <numberRows>
              Specifies the horizontal or vertical dimension of a grid in  the
              map, measured in row height. If you specify a value less than 1,
              the software uses 1.

              Default: 10

              Upper limit: 100

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each reportDensityMap parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man reportDensityMap.

       -ignoreBlock {true|false}
              Skips block cells instances from both supply and demand calcula-
              tion.

              Default: false

       -ignoreFiller {true|false}
              Ignores the density of fillers in the post-filler  density  heat
              map to show the density of standard cells .

              Default: false

       -threshold <density>
              Specifies a threshold density value for the grid. Any grid under
              the threshold value is not reported. The value must be positive.

              Default: 0.75

              Upper limit: 2.0

Example
       The  following are output from command reportDensityMap. It generates a
       map with default threshold of 0.75 and measured in row height:

       powerDomain TOP: bins with density > 0.75 = 0.519 % ( 6 / 1156 )

       bin size: 59 sites by 10 row(s). total 1156 bins ( 34 by 34 )

       density range #bins %

       0.75 - 0.8 5 0.4325

       0.8 - 0.85 1 0.08651

       total 6 0.519

